reading all input into memory might be dangeruous if translating a HUGE input file. Why not just open a fd or assign to sys.stdin based on args.source/input, like this (also outside of this function):

if args.input is not None:
  input_fd = sockeye.utils.smart_open(args.input)
else:
  input_fd = sys.stdin

with this you can directly call _translate and iterate over it.

